Comment: Hi everyone, I am taking a trip down memory lane, in fact 12 years ago.  This is my second local Bury League Match.  This is Cambridge City Chess Club playing against the ICI Sheepdogs in a place called Stowmarket somewhere in Suffolk, United Kingdom.  I was on board 4 of 4 in that match.  I had to do the driving, so it was very nice to drive home after what happened in this match.

36............. such as Bc3# - Old Matey Strikes out of the blue!  Incredibly the white king has no squares to go to, the check cannot be blocked, the bishop cannot be captured so all this equals ........... CHECKMATE!!

What a finale to a seemingly boring endgame!
